      "onchain_auto/0x3335a88bb18fd3b6824b59af62b50ce494143333/rubic-bridge-base/contracts/BridgeBase.sol:319"
    ],
    "claim": "The chosen integrator is taken directly from user-controlled calldata, and the contract never authenticates that the caller is actually routing through that integrator. If any integrator is configured with lower custom fees, every user can claim that address and receive the same pricing.",
    "impact": "Custom partner pricing becomes a public fee-bypass mechanism. Users can permissionlessly route under zero-fee or reduced-fee integrator profiles, reducing or eliminating protocol revenue and undermining whatever economics or partner segmentation operators intended.",
    "paths": [
      "A manager configures an integrator with cheaper fees than the default platform schedule.",
      "An arbitrary user sets `_params.integrator` to that partner's address.",
      "`accrueFixedCryptoFee` and `_calculateFee` apply the discounted fee profile without any proof of authorization."
    ]
  },
