    ],
    "claim": "`RequestSent` emits the user-supplied `BaseCrossChainParams` after any successful external call, but the native path does not validate `_params.srcInputAmount` at all and neither path proves that the downstream router actually initiated the advertised bridge. The event is therefore not a trustworthy record of what was executed.",
    "impact": "If any off-chain relayer, accounting system, or rewards logic keys off `RequestSent`, an attacker can spoof recipient/amount/chain metadata with a successful but semantically different router call. That can lead to false credits, incorrect settlements, or bogus cross-chain processing.",
    "paths": [
      "The caller supplies arbitrary `BaseCrossChainParams` values.",
      "In `routerCallNative`, the forwarded value is derived from `msg.value`, not from `_params.srcInputAmount`.",
      "After any successful external call, `eventEmitter` publishes the unchecked struct as `RequestSent`."
    ]
  }
